<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>blazor-wasm on Alfero Chingono</title><link>https://www.chingono.com/tags/blazor-wasm/</link><description>Recent content in blazor-wasm on Alfero Chingono</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 07 Apr 2021 18:39:49 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://www.chingono.com/tags/blazor-wasm/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Dockerizing Blazor Wasm Application</title><link>https://www.chingono.com/blog/2021/04/07/dockerizing-blazor-wasm-application/</link><pubDate>Wed, 07 Apr 2021 18:39:49 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.chingono.com/blog/2021/04/07/dockerizing-blazor-wasm-application/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://www.chingono.com/blog/2021/04/07/dockerizing-blazor-wasm-application/cover.jpg" alt="Featured image of post Dockerizing Blazor Wasm Application" />&lt;p>This is a continuation of my previous post; &lt;a class="link" href="https://www.chingono.com/blog/2021/03/04/waiting-docker-service-container-port-ready/" >Waiting for Docker Service Container Port to Be Ready&lt;/a>. After reading &lt;a class="link" href="https://www.c-sharpcorner.com/article/dockerizing-blazor-wasm-application/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
